com.ibm.watson.dsm.platform.topology.registry.fixed

Class FixedRegistry

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ibm.watson.dsm.platform.topology.registry.AbstractApplicationRegistry
      • com.ibm.watson.dsm.platform.topology.registry.fixed.FixedRegistry
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IDistributedApplicationRegistry

    public class FixedRegistry
extends AbstractApplicationRegistry
    Allows the definition a fixed set of peer registrations from a text file. The format of the text file is 1 line per registration, with each line formatted according to ApplicationRegistration.parseRegistration(String).

    This may be instantiated in the runtime through dsm.properties and it's application.registry property. In addition, this class defines uses the FIXED_REGISTRATIONS_FILE_PROPERTY property to define the name and location of the registrations file. If not specified, it defaults to DEFAULT_REGISTRATIONS_FILE.

    Author:
    dawood
